<div id="review_915721385" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/915721385" />
    <a title="Judy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/854592-judy"><img alt="Judy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1256675984p2/854592.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/915721385?book_show_action=true">Apr 20, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Judy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Judy" href="/user/show/854592-judy">Judy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer915721385" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5019229655316407120">Full Disclosure--I am addicted to The Daily Show. When I miss the show, I can be found at my desk at work sneaking a peek at the internet repeat. So this was absolutely the book for me. A totally entertaining look at the &quot;citizen&apos;s guide of democracy inaction&quot;. Lots of moments when I found myself laughing out loud. That wouldn&apos;t be so bad, but again I was at my desk. I really need to get a grip on my behavior. Loved this book.</span>
  <span id="freeText5019229655316407120" style="display:none">Full Disclosure--I am addicted to The Daily Show. When I miss the show, I can be found at my desk at work sneaking a peek at the internet repeat. So this was absolutely the book for me. A totally entertaining look at the "citizen's guide of democracy inaction". Lots of moments when I found myself laughing out loud. That wouldn't be so bad, but again I was at my desk. I really need to get a grip on my behavior. Loved this book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5019229655316407120" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
